In the armed forces, age is just a number but hierarchy? That’s everything. You could be 28, glowing and thriving, and still be called “Auntie” by someone barely 2 years younger to you just because your husband’s colleagues are their dads. My husband?Promoted to uncle at 23 by a senior’s son. Unexpected titles are part of the package—just like the uniform.

But if there’s one thing that never changes, it’s the style. Chiffon saris flowing with poise, big aviators that mean business, pearl necklaces worn like medals, and a whole lot of grace and wisdom. Timeless respect, timeless fashion and a little humour in between. It is what it is.👒🫡✨

He has always held my hand in one, and my bag in the other from the very first day we met.
Once I asked, “Don’t you feel weird? What will people think?”
And he said, “Kuch toh log kahenge, logon ka kaam hai kehna… logon ke chakkar mein jeena aur tumse pyaar karna chhod du?”
Haye… uss line pe aisi giri ki aaj tak uth nahi paayi 💌

Wearing these beautiful sarees from @ke.sari.ka — a brand close to my heart, run by a fellow fauji wife. 💛

I made piping hot samosas and told him, “Let’s enjoy them outside.” I asked him to sit beside me, but no — my boy wanted to stand and eat. And guess what? He dropped the piping hot filling on me. 😂😂
And the moment it happened, he hit me with the fastest “I’m sorry” ever — before I could escalate and throw him off the balcony. 😆

A lot of people are going to ask, ‘How come you had the camera on?’
Well, I had set it up to capture a peaceful moment of us enjoying our cozy tea time one last time before he left…
And there was absolutely nothing peaceful about it. 😂😂😂
